TITLE: Initializing an Acode Plugin with Command Registration in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to initialize an Acode plugin by setting up the plugin init function. It registers a custom command with key bindings that displays HTML content in a page when executed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/acode-foundation/acode-plugin-docs/blob/main/docs/plugin-essentials/core-file.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
acode.setPluginInit('com.example.plugin', (baseUrl, $page, cache) => {
  const { commands } = editorManager.editor;
  commands.addCommand({
    name: 'example-plugin',
    bindKey: { win: 'Ctrl-Alt-E', mac: 'Command-Alt-E' },
    exec: () => {
      $page.innerHTML = `
        <h1>Example Plugin</h1>
        <p>This is an example plugin.</p>
      `;
      $page.show();
    },
  });
});
```

