TITLE: Creating URL-Safe Strings with Url.safe() Method
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the usage of the safe() method to encode each component of a URL, returning a URL-safe string.
SOURCE: https://github.com/acode-foundation/acode-plugin-docs/blob/main/docs/utilities/url.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const safeUrl = Url.safe('https://www.example.com/path/to/file.html?query=string#hash');
// Output: 'https://www.example.com/path/to/file.html%3Fquery%3Dstring%23hash'
```

